HEADWORD: Pruinose
<hw>Pru"i*nose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pruinosus</ets>, fr. <ets>pruina</ets> hoarfrost.]</ety>
<def>Frosty; covered with fine scales, hairs, dust, bloom, or the like,
so as to give the appearance of frost.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pruinous</ent>⟦br⟧
